author: Scott Prather
title: LSU Tigers Lewis Neal, Vadal Alexander Honored By SEC Today
text:
LSU Tigers Lewis Neal, Vadal Alexander Honored By SEC Today By Scott Prather October 19, 2015 12:13 PM Share on Twitter Photo by Chris Graythen/Getty Images 
LSU defensive end Lewis Neal (pictured) and right tackle Vadal Alexander were honored by the SEC today after their standout performances in Saturday night’s win over Florida . 
Neal was all over the field for the Tiger defense, finishing the game with 10 tackles and 3 sacks. The junior from Wilson, North Carolina was named SEC defensive player of the week today. 
Alexander, a senior from New Orleans, led an LSU offensive line that paved away for 221 rushing yards against a vaunted Gator defense. Alexander was credited with 13 knockdowns and did not allow a sack. As a result, he was named the SEC offensive lineman of the week. 
Alexander received the same honor in week 2 after LSU’s win over Mississippi State. 
LSU (6-0) will host Western Kentucky (6-1) in a non-conference matchup Saturday night at Tiger Stadium. Kickoff is set for 6:00.
